Title:[Catalogue Entry] collated against TEI data - unmatched items
Description:[Catalogue Entry] collated against TEI data - unmatched items. But we are currently massively overreporting, e.g. WangShumin_2005.xml catalogue contains refs to P.3481 meaning Pelliot chinois 3481. How is it the current system finds and display the correct catalogue entry for this? See http://idp.bl.uk/database/oo_Loader.a4D?pm=pelliot%20chinois%203481. We need to use similar logic to connect the two during collation... WARNING: [Catalogue Entry] table seems to contain some corrupt (non-unicode) data which causes ODBC SQL to introduce even more strange characters - this currently causes bogus in place of final character in Stein Photo 1/3(10) for example. See other report in this script for some ways of getting around this???
